  "prompt": "What causes a pulsating feeling under the left rib cage?",
  "response": "A pulsating feeling under the left rib cage can be caused by various factors, ranging from benign to more serious conditions. Some possible causes include:\n\n1. **Muscle Spasms or Strain**: Overexertion or injury to the muscles in the area can lead to spasms or twitching sensations.\n\n2. **Gas and Digestive Issues**: Trapped gas in the intestines can cause a pulsating or moving sensation. Conditions like irritable bowel syndrome (IBS) can also lead to similar symptoms.\n\n3. **Splenic Pulsation**: The spleen is located under the left rib cage. Certain conditions, like an enlarged spleen (splenomegaly), can sometimes cause pulsating feelings.\n\n4. **Aortic Aneurysm**: Though less common, an aneurysm in the abdominal aorta can cause a pulsating sensation. This condition requires prompt medical attention.\n\n5. **Heart-related Issues**: Though the heart is more centrally located, issues like palpitations can sometimes be felt towards the left side of the chest.\n\n6. **Nerve Irritation or Compression**: Issues like pinched nerves or nerve irritation can cause pulsating or twitching sensations.\n\n7. **Psychosomatic Causes**: Anxiety and stress can lead to physical sensations, including pulsating feelings in various parts of the body.\n\nIf you are experiencing a persistent or concerning pulsating feeling under your left rib cage, it is advisable to consult a healthcare professional for a proper diagnosis and appropriate treatment.",
